text: So I‚Äôll probably get slammed for this but here goes anyway. ¬†  When the original Little Orphan Annie was written, chronologically we were a lot closer to a time where there was a strong bias against Irish people. ¬†By making Annie red haired, it was implied that she was of Irish descent, and by extension, the audience would have inherently known that was part of the bias against her.¬†Changing Annie‚Äôs race to African American replicates this same dynamic in modern society.¬† Casting Annie as black in 2014 is a much more true to the original character than casting her as a caucasian red head.

text: I am NOT a racist person by any means. Actually very far from it. I respect blacks browns whites etc equally and am offended by anyone who hates on someone just because of their skin color. It's just ridiculous. But I am going to say this..... TV and movies has become pathetic in the past decade when it comes to race. TV shows, movies, Lifetime movies, commercials, etc have all just gone completely overboard with their sense of equality and making their pathetic attempt at putting black people up on a pedestal. There isn't a commercial on TV these days that doesn't have an equal amount of white and black people with an asian thrown in for good measure. They have BET channel made just for the black race, and now we get ANNIE as a black girl? I'm sorry but this is beyond insulting to all races.  If there was a channel called 'White People's Entertainment' it wouldn't be on air for a week before they got slammed with a lawsuit. If Annie was originally black and this movie had her as a white girl, there would be so much criticism and hatred from black people. What if they brought back the Cosby Show but as a white family?? How would that sit with you?  Yes, okay? We get it. We're all equal. But they are taking this bullshit propaganda wayyyy too far! It's almost insulting to all races. And if you want my honest opinion, I think there are more racist black people in America today than white because they hold a grudge and have for centuries. I also think that a lot of black people feed off of racism for attention.  Everyone, especially Hollywood, needs to leave well enough alone and do things normally. This whole black Annie in the ghetto is just taking shit way too far and should certainly not be labeled as a remake to a classic movie that has shaped many childhoods. Bottom line: this movie is fucking pathetic.
author: Aaron the Atheist
